<item>
            <title>[NET-178] Support for unciode character is missing</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/NET-178</link>
                <project id="12310487" key="NET">Commons Net</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m using sendMessageData() method of SMTPClient class to obtain a Writer object. The mails i need to send contain unicode characters. The Writer which sendMessageData() method returns, uses &quot;ISO-8859-1&quot; encoding which does not provide support for all unicode characters. Also the encoding is not configurable i.e. there is no method through which i can set the encoding to something else. This issue has delayed the release of my project. I think this is a very major issue which needs to be addressed as soon as possible. Unicode support should be provided by this API or encoding must be made configurable. Please provide me a workaround for this issue. It&apos;s very urgent!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
